181
00:07:07,640 --> 00:07:09,050
Its chief executive said,

182
00:07:09,050 --> 00:07:10,910
“We're a little country...

183
00:07:10,910 --> 00:07:12,570
we've got to step into this space.”

184
00:07:12,570 --> 00:07:15,640
Aww, like a Hobbit.

185
00:07:15,640 --> 00:07:16,660
The problem is,

186
00:07:16,660 --> 00:07:19,970
if you actually put a Hobbit in front of a
Dragon,

187
00:07:19,970 --> 00:07:22,010
the dragon will bite his head off.

188
00:07:22,010 --> 00:07:24,120
Sorry Bilbo.

189
00:07:24,120 --> 00:07:25,870
Countries and business around the world

190
00:07:25,870 --> 00:07:28,760
have been making this mistake for years.

191
00:07:28,760 --> 00:07:30,040
People see the gold,

192
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:32,530
and forget there’s a giant dragon.

193
00:07:32,530 --> 00:07:34,280
So how has China trade worked out

194
00:07:34,280 --> 00:07:36,920
so far for Air New Zealand?

195
00:07:36,920 --> 00:07:39,160
Over the 13 years its been in China,

196
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:42,330
Air New Zealand has lost 100 million dollars.

197
00:07:42,330 --> 00:07:44,020
That’s because the Chinese government

198
00:07:44,020 --> 00:07:46,640
gives preference to Chinese airlines.

199
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:49,060
But surely just because this is the same story

200
00:07:49,060 --> 00:07:51,150
that happens again and again,

201
00:07:51,150 --> 00:07:53,450
doesn’t mean tomorrow won’t be different.

202
00:07:53,450 --> 00:07:55,460
So hand over the ring.

